text: Dan Moody is an outdoor sculpture depicting the politician of the same name by Lucas Adams, installed outside the Williamson County Courthouse in Georgetown, Texas, United States. The statue was installed on October 14, 2016. ==See also== * 2016 in art ==References== Category:2016 establishments in Texas Category:2016 sculptures Category:Bronze sculptures in Texas Category:Monuments and memorials in Texas Category:Outdoor sculptures in Texas Category:Sculptures of men in Texas Category:Statues in Texas
